headline: America’s Cattle Crisis: a Shrinking Herd, Soaring Beef Prices, and Little Relief in Sight
summary: It’s late morning in Central Texas Hill Country, and a Black Baldy is prodded into a small auditorium of Western hats and dusty ball caps.  “It’s going to go as a packer animal,” says Tim Niedecken, who works for the Jordan Cattle Auction.
